            <title>[SUREFIRE-1088] When test fail during initialization the test execution time can result in a large negative number.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-1088</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For example it will print out this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; Time elapsed: -1,317,678.69 sec  &amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt; ERROR!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This happened in a call to @BeforeClass method and was specifically when a class was not found when loading in a spring context. The later is not that important because we have seen it happen in other cases.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
