                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14456312" author="agudian" created="Sat, 27 Sep 2014 17:07:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m having trouble reproducing it. You filled in Affects Version with 2.16. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you try if it happens also in 2.17 in your case?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If so, a small test project to reproduce the issue would be great.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456293" author="ddcruver" created="Tue, 30 Sep 2014 18:20:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I believe this issue still effects 2.17. We get a case where we have a failing test that causes this to happen atleast once a week.  Unfortunately I am unable to produce an example that reproduces it.  I will let you know if I have better luck tomorrow. Thank You.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456162" author="agudian" created="Sat, 4 Oct 2014 16:22:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Daniel: your surefire configuration would be a good start to see what kind of forkCount / reuseForks, parallel, provider configuration you use.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456272" author="ddcruver" created="Wed, 8 Oct 2014 11:18:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;redirectTestOutputToFile&amp;gt;true&amp;lt;/redirectTestOutputToFile&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;testFailureIgnore&amp;gt;true&amp;lt;/testFailureIgnore&amp;gt;  // This is the settings that the CI server is using so we can get all test failures instead of first.&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;forkCount&amp;gt;0.25C&amp;lt;/forkCount&amp;gt;  // Use 1/4 of build servers processor cores because it has 4 agents, trying to avoid using full machine.&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;reuseForks&amp;gt;false&amp;lt;/reuseForks&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are also using excludedGroups, includes, systemPropertyVariables but believe that is irreverent.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456259" author="agudian" created="Sat, 11 Oct 2014 16:08:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That description was enough for me to be able to finally reporduce it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s fixed with commit 080aa5f612382cd1bf6e47c4322bd855ad3b4fed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;@Daniel: if you have the possibility, you could test-drive the fix with the 2.18-SNAPSHOT version.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks again for the report!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456318" author="ddcruver" created="Mon, 13 Oct 2014 11:34:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No problem. Thanks for looking into it with the lack of information glad what I gave was just enough.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Good for us but none of our builds are failing in a way to reproduce the original issue, but it happen enough times to us that it may happen again.  When I get a chance I will have to see if I can find one in our build servers history and try to use the new snapshot.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17994491" author="olamy" created="Fri, 4 Jul 2025 07:22:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This project has moved from Jira to GitHub Issues. This issue was migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-surefire/issues/1469&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;apache/maven-surefire#1469&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
